\dfrac{6}{C} = \dfrac{30}{360} = \dfrac{1}{12}\quad \implies \quad C = 6\times 12  \implies C=72
C = d\pi = 2\pi r
C = 72 = 2 \pi r 
\implies r = \dfrac{72}{2\pi} = \dfrac{36}{\pi}
